sentences.english: Leave the key in the lock.
Objective To study the surgical techniques with keyhole operation for treatment of the intracranial lesions.
sentences.chinese: 目的探讨采用锁孔手术治疗颅内病变的手术技术。

sentences.english: Objective To explore the clinical application of keyhole craniotomy microsurgery in neurosurgery.
sentences.chinese: 目的探讨锁孔入路显微手术在神经外科的应用。

sentences.english: She watches intently from her keyhole behind the door of the forgotten room.
sentences.chinese: 她在忘却之室，从门的锁孔密切地注视。

sentences.english: The key clicked as it turned in the lock.
sentences.chinese: 钥匙在锁孔里转动，发出喀哒的声音。

sentences.english: Jim turn the key in the lock and opened the door.
sentences.chinese: 吉姆把钥匙插在锁孔里，转动一下，打开了门。

sentences.english: Hook and eye keyhole zigzag seam at the waist before.
sentences.chinese: 钩眼锁孔前和锯齿缝在腰。

sentences.english: Objective To explore the application of neuronavigation in keyhole surgery.
sentences.chinese: 目的探讨神经导航技术在神经外科锁孔手术中的应用。

sentences.english: Objectives To study the exposure of the structure by microsurgery through interforniceal interpositum keyhole approach to the pineal region.
sentences.chinese: 目的研究经穹窿间中间帆锁孔入路的手术显露。

sentences.english: But we have discovered another keyhole and another key which can lock the door.
sentences.chinese: 但是我们发现了另一个锁孔和另一把可以锁门的钥匙。

sentences.english: A keyhole pattern in the base provides additional security and stability when needed.
sentences.chinese: 甲锁孔格局基础提供额外的安全性和稳定性必要时。

sentences.english: Objective To investigate the value of orbital roof osteotomy via supraorbital keyhole approach.
sentences.chinese: 目的探讨眶上锁孔入路中去除眶顶的应用价值。

sentences.english: Conclusion The surgery for the lesions in the pineal region is feasible via the transoccipito-supratentorial key hole operation approach.
sentences.chinese: 结论经枕幕上锁孔手术入路行松果体区手术是可行的。

sentences.english: Peter Goldthwaite was inserting a key into the lock.
What worried him was that his broken key jammed the lock.
sentences.chinese: 让他焦急不安的是折断的钥匙把锁孔给卡住了。

definition: variant of 門閂|门闩[men2 shuan1]
bolt (for locking a window, cabinet etc)/(electrical) plug
horizontal bar to hold a door closed (made of wood or metal)/door bolt
to pull out/to pull a lever
